# Plan: PulseBoard Channel Plugin

## Context

Add a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group chat) and can also send direct messages (DMs) to other users. The plugin must support both `direct` and `group` chat types with a 4000-character text chunk limit. It must follow the same extension structure, boundary rules, and SDK patterns used by existing bundled plugins (Nostr for single-account DM-only; IRC for multi-chat-type reference).

**Constraint:** Only create new files inside `extensions/pulseboard/`. Do not modify any existing files.

---

## File Tree to Create

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json        # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                # Package metadata + openclaw.channel block
├── index.ts                    # defineChannelPluginEntry entry point
├── setup-entry.ts              # defineSetupPluginEntry entry point
├── api.ts                      # Public re-export barrel (→ runtime-api.ts)
├── runtime-api.ts              # Private SDK re-export barrel (openclaw/plugin-sdk/*)
└── src/
    ├── channel.ts              # createChatChannelPlugin — main plugin definition
    ├── channel.test.ts         # Vitest tests (metadata, config, normalization)
    ├── client.ts               # Fictional PulseBoard client stub
    ├── config-schema.ts        # Zod schema for channels.pulseboard.*
    ├── normalize.ts            # Target + allowEntry normalization helpers
    ├── runtime.ts              # createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>
    ├── setup-surface.ts        # ChannelSetupAdapter + ChannelSetupWizard
    └── types.ts                # ResolvedPulseboardAccount + account resolvers
```

---

## Critical Files to Read First (Reference)

| Reference File | Why |
|---|---|
| `extensions/nostr/src/channel.ts` | Full createChatChannelPlugin pattern for single-account DM plugin |
| `extensions/nostr/src/types.ts` | Account resolution pattern with DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID |
| `extensions/nostr/src/setup-surface.ts` | Setup wizard + adapter pattern |
| `extensions/nostr/src/config-schema.ts` | Config schema imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives` |
| `extensions/nostr/runtime-api.ts` | Runtime barrel pattern (`export * from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/nostr"`) |
| `extensions/irc/src/inbound.ts` | How IRC handles group dispatch via `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` |
| `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` | Group policy + directory adapter patterns |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest. The `configSchema` stays empty (schema details live in the Zod validation).

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

### Step 2 — `package.json`

No external runtime dependencies (PulseBoard is fictional; the client is a stub). Use `openclaw` as a `devDependency` / `peerDependency` only. Include the full `openclaw.channel` block.

Key fields:
- `name`: `@openclaw/pulseboard`
- `version`: match current repo version (e.g. `2026.4.2`)
- `openclaw.extensions`: `["./index.ts"]`
- `openclaw.setupEntry`: `"./setup-entry.ts"`
- `openclaw.channel.id`: `"pulseboard"`
- `openclaw.channel.label`: `"PulseBoard"`
- `openclaw.channel.selectionLabel`: `"PulseBoard (boards + DMs)"`
- `openclaw.channel.docsPath`: `"/channels/pulseboard"`
- `openclaw.channel.docsLabel`: `"pulseboard"`
- `openclaw.channel.blurb`: `"Real-time bulletin board messaging; boards and direct messages."`
- `openclaw.channel.order`: `60`
- `openclaw.channel.quickstartAllowFrom`: `true`
- `openclaw.install.npmSpec`: `"@openclaw/pulseboard"`
- `openclaw.release.publishToNpm`: `true`

---

### Step 3 — `src/runtime.ts`

Thin runtime store — identical pattern to `extensions/nostr/src/runtime.ts`.

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "../api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseboardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseboardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseboardRuntime, setPulseboardRuntime };
```

---

### Step 4 — `src/config-schema.ts`

Zod schema for `channels.pulseboard.*`. Import all schema primitives from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives` (same as Nostr). Key fields:

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `name` | `string?` | Account display name |
| `enabled` | `boolean?` | Toggle account on/off |
| `token` | `SecretInput?` | API credential (env: `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN`) |
| `serverUrl` | `string.url()?` | PulseBoard server base URL |
| `username` | `string?` | Username on the platform |
| `dmPolicy` | `DmPolicySchema?` | `"pairing" \| "allowlist" \| "open" \| "disabled"` |
| `allowFrom` | `AllowFromListSchema` | Allowlisted DM sender usernames |
| `groupPolicy` | `GroupPolicySchema?` | Board access: `"allowlist" \| "open" \| "disabled"` |
| `boards` | `z.array(z.string())?` | Auto-subscribe board names |
| `markdown` | `MarkdownConfigSchema` | Markdown table rendering overrides |

Export `PulseboardConfigSchema`, `type PulseboardConfig`, and `pulseboardChannelConfigSchema` (the JSON Schema for the Control UI, built via `buildChannelConfigSchema`).

Imports needed:
```typescript
import {
  AllowFromListSchema,
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  GroupPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives";
import { buildSecretInputSchema } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";
```

> **Note:** `GroupPolicySchema` is confirmed exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives` (re-exported there from `src/config/zod-schema.core.ts`). Verify it is in that subpath at implementation time; if not, import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema` instead.

---

### Step 5 — `src/normalize.ts`

Two pure helpers for normalizing platform identifiers:

```typescript
/**
 * Normalize a PulseBoard messaging target.
 * Board names start with "#"; DM targets are bare usernames.
 * Strips "pulseboard:", "board:", "user:" prefixes; lowercases.
 */
export function normalizePulseboardTarget(raw: string): string { ... }

/**
 * Normalize a PulseBoard allowlist entry.
 * Strips whitespace, prefixes; lowercases; returns null for empty.
 */
export function normalizePulseboardAllowEntry(
  entry: string,
): string | "*" | null { ... }

/**
 * Check whether a sender username matches an allowlist.
 */
export function isPulseboardSenderAllowed(
  senderUsername: string,
  allowFrom: string[],
): boolean { ... }
```

Normalization rules:
- Board names → strip leading `pulseboard:`, `board:`, or `#` prefix; add canonical `#` prefix; lowercase
- DM usernames → strip `pulseboard:`, `user:`, `@` prefix; lowercase; trim
- Allowlist `"*"` is a wildcard

---

### Step 6 — `src/client.ts`

Fictional PulseBoard client. Since the platform does not exist, this is a typed stub. It defines the contract without making real network calls. A real implementation would connect via WebSocket or HTTP long-poll.

Key exported types and class:

```typescript
export interface PulseboardDirectMessage {
  from: string;
  to: string;
  text: string;
  messageId: string;
  timestamp: number; // Unix ms
}

export interface PulseboardBoardMessage {
  from: string;       // sender username
  board: string;      // board name (without #)
  text: string;
  messageId: string;
  timestamp: number;
}

export interface PulseboardClientOptions {
  serverUrl: string;
  token: string;
  username: string;
}

export interface PulseboardClientHandlers {
  onDirectMessage: (msg: PulseboardDirectMessage) => Promise<void>;
  onBoardMessage: (msg: PulseboardBoardMessage) => Promise<void>;
  onError: (err: Error, context: string) => void;
  onConnect: () => void;
  onDisconnect: () => void;
}

export class PulseboardClient {
  constructor(private readonly opts: PulseboardClientOptions) {}

  /** Connect and register event handlers. Stub: no real network I/O. */
  async connect(handlers: PulseboardClientHandlers): Promise<void> { ... }

  /** Disconnect from the platform. */
  async disconnect(): Promise<void> { ... }

  /** Send a DM to a user. Returns the platform-assigned messageId. */
  async sendDirectMessage(
    to: string,
    text: string,
  ): Promise<{ messageId: string }> {
    return { messageId: `pb-dm-${Date.now()}` };
  }

  /** Send a message to a named board. Returns the platform-assigned messageId. */
  async sendBoardMessage(
    board: string,
    text: string,
  ): Promise<{ messageId: string }> {
    return { messageId: `pb-board-${Date.now()}` };
  }
}
```

Add a brief comment explaining the stub nature: "PulseBoard is a fictional platform. This client simulates the expected API shape. A production client would maintain a WebSocket connection to opts.serverUrl authenticated with opts.token."

---

### Step 7 — `src/types.ts`

Account resolution — modeled after `extensions/nostr/src/types.ts`.

```typescript
export interface PulseboardAccountConfig {
  enabled?: boolean;
  name?: string;
  token?: SecretInput;
  serverUrl?: string;
  username?: string;
  dmPolicy?: "pairing" | "allowlist" | "open" | "disabled";
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groupPolicy?: "allowlist" | "open" | "disabled";
  boards?: string[];
  markdown?: unknown;
}

export interface ResolvedPulseboardAccount {
  accountId: string;
  name?: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  configured: boolean;   // true when token + serverUrl + username all present
  token: string;
  serverUrl: string;
  username: string;
  boards: string[];
  config: PulseboardAccountConfig;
}
```

Functions:
- `listPulseboardAccountIds(cfg): string[]` — returns `[DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID]` when token is present; empty otherwise
- `resolveDefaultPulseboardAccountId(cfg): string` — delegates to `resolveListedDefaultAccountId`
- `resolvePulseboardAccount({ cfg, accountId? }): ResolvedPulseboardAccount` — reads from `cfg.channels.pulseboard`; `configured` requires all three of token, serverUrl, username

Imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id`, `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution`, `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input`.

---

### Step 8 — `src/setup-surface.ts`

Two exports: `pulseboardSetupAdapter` (`ChannelSetupAdapter`) and `pulseboardSetupWizard` (`ChannelSetupWizard`). Modeled after `extensions/nostr/src/setup-surface.ts`.

**Setup Adapter** (`pulseboardSetupAdapter`):
- `resolveAccountId`: returns `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`
- `applyAccountName`: patches `channels.pulseboard.name` via `patchTopLevelChannelConfigSection`
- `validateInput`: validates token non-empty, serverUrl is a valid URL, username non-empty
- `applyAccountConfig`: applies token, serverUrl, username, and optionally boards

**Setup Wizard** (`pulseboardSetupWizard`):
- `channel`: `"pulseboard"`
- `resolveAccountIdForConfigure`: `() => DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`
- `resolveShouldPromptAccountIds`: `() => false`
- `status`: `createStandardChannelSetupStatus` — configured when token + serverUrl + username present
- `introNote`: explains PulseBoard concepts (boards vs DMs, token setup)
- `envShortcut`: detect `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN`, offer to use it
- `credentials`: collect `token` (`PULSEBOARD_TOKEN` env var)
- `textInputs`: collect `serverUrl` (validates URL), `username`
- `allowFrom`: `createTopLevelChannelParsedAllowFromPrompt` for DM allowlist
- `dmPolicy`: `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicy`
- `disable`: patches `enabled: false`

Import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup`, `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-setup`, `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input`.

---

### Step 9 — `src/channel.ts`

Core plugin file. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`.

**Module-level state:**
```typescript
// Active client handles, keyed by accountId
const activeClients = new Map<string, PulseboardClient>();
```

**Config adapter** (`pulseboardConfigAdapter`): created via `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter` with `sectionKey: "pulseboard"`.

**DM security resolver** (`resolvePulseboardDmPolicy`): created via `createScopedDmSecurityResolver`.

**Plugin definition** — `export const pulseboardPlugin: ChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseboardAccount>`:

```typescript
createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: {
      id: "pulseboard",
      label: "PulseBoard",
      selectionLabel: "PulseBoard",
      docsPath: "/channels/pulseboard",
      docsLabel: "pulseboard",
      blurb: "Real-time bulletin board messaging; boards and direct messages.",
      order: 60,
    },
    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      media: false,
    },
    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseboardConfigSchema),
    setup: pulseboardSetupAdapter,
    setupWizard: pulseboardSetupWizard,
    config: {
      ...pulseboardConfigAdapter,
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) => describeAccountSnapshot({ ... }),
    },
    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: (target) => normalizePulseboardTarget(target),
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: (input) => {
          const t = input.trim();
          // Boards start with # or "board:"; DM usernames are word chars
          return t.startsWith("#") || t.startsWith("board:") || /^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$/.test(t);
        },
        hint: "<#board-name|username>",
      },
      resolveOutboundSessionRoute: (params) => {
        // If target starts with # → group board; otherwise direct DM
        const isBoard = params.to.startsWith("#");
        return buildChannelOutboundSessionRoute({
          peer: isBoard
            ? { kind: "group", id: params.to }
            : { kind: "direct", id: params.to },
          chatType: isBoard ? "group" : "direct",
          from: params.from,
          to: params.to,
          sessionKey: `${params.accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID}:${params.to}`,
          baseSessionKey: `${params.accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID}:${params.to}`,
        });
      },
    },
    status: {
      ...createComputedAccountStatusAdapter<ResolvedPulseboardAccount>({ ... }),
    },
    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        // 1. Validate account.configured
        // 2. Get runtime + create pairing controller
        // 3. Create PulseboardClient and call connect()
        // 4. In onDirectMessage handler:
        //      - Resolve DM access via resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime
        //      - Dispatch via dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime
        //      - deliver callback calls client.sendDirectMessage
        // 5. In onBoardMessage handler:
        //      - Apply group policy (groupPolicy: allowlist/open/disabled)
        //      - Dispatch via dispatchInboundReplyWithBase with ChatType: "group"
        //      - deliver callback calls client.sendBoardMessage
        // 6. Store client in activeClients map
        // 7. Return { stop: () => { client.disconnect(); activeClients.delete(accountId) } }
      },
    },
  },
  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseboardUsername",
      message: "Your pairing request has been approved!",
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => normalizePulseboardAllowEntry(entry) ?? entry,
      notify: async ({ id, message }) => {
        const client = activeClients.get(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID);
        if (client) await client.sendDirectMessage(id, message);
      },
    },
  },
  security: {
    resolveDmPolicy: resolvePulseboardDmPolicy,
  },
  outbound: {
    deliveryMode: "direct",
    textChunkLimit: 4000,
    sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId }) => {
      const aid = accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID;
      const client = activeClients.get(aid);
      if (!client) throw new Error(`PulseBoard client not running for account ${aid}`);
      // Resolve markdown table mode, convert tables
      const isBoard = to.startsWith("#");
      const result = isBoard
        ? await client.sendBoardMessage(to.slice(1), text ?? "")
        : await client.sendDirectMessage(to, text ?? "");
      return attachChannelToResult("pulseboard", {
        to,
        messageId: result.messageId,
      });
    },
  },
});
```

**Group dispatch detail** (inside `onBoardMessage` handler in `startAccount`):
- Check `account.config.groupPolicy` (default `"open"`): if `"disabled"`, drop; if `"allowlist"`, verify board is in `account.config.boards`
- Dispatch via `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` (import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch`) passing `ChatType: "group"`, `GroupSubject: boardName`

> **Import path note:** `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` lives in `src/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch.ts`. The package.json exports ~100+ SDK subpaths; verify the exact path name at implementation time. The IRC plugin accesses it via `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`; for PulseBoard, try `openclaw/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch` or `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-dispatch` as candidates.

---

### Step 10 — `runtime-api.ts`

Since there is no pre-existing `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade, this barrel re-exports directly from the relevant general SDK subpaths. This keeps channel.ts, types.ts, and setup-surface.ts free of scattered SDK path strings.

