## Context

Add a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group chat) and can also send direct messages (DMs) to other users. The plugin must support both `direct` and `group` chat types with a 4000-character text chunk limit. It must follow the same extension structure, boundary rules, and SDK patterns used by existing bundled plugins (Nostr for single-account DM-only; IRC for multi-chat-type reference).

