### Step 9 — `src/channel.ts`

Core plugin file. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`.

**Module-level state:**
```typescript
// Active client handles, keyed by accountId
const activeClients = new Map<string, PulseboardClient>();
```

**Config adapter** (`pulseboardConfigAdapter`): created via `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter` with `sectionKey: "pulseboard"`.

**DM security resolver** (`resolvePulseboardDmPolicy`): created via `createScopedDmSecurityResolver`.

**Plugin definition** — `export const pulseboardPlugin: ChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseboardAccount>`:

```typescript
createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: {
      id: "pulseboard",
      label: "PulseBoard",
      selectionLabel: "PulseBoard",
      docsPath: "/channels/pulseboard",
      docsLabel: "pulseboard",
      blurb: "Real-time bulletin board messaging; boards and direct messages.",
      order: 60,
    },
    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      media: false,
    },
    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseboardConfigSchema),
    setup: pulseboardSetupAdapter,
    setupWizard: pulseboardSetupWizard,
    config: {
      ...pulseboardConfigAdapter,
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) => describeAccountSnapshot({ ... }),
    },
    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: (target) => normalizePulseboardTarget(target),
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: (input) => {
          const t = input.trim();
          // Boards start with # or "board:"; DM usernames are word chars
          return t.startsWith("#") || t.startsWith("board:") || /^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$/.test(t);
        },
        hint: "<#board-name|username>",
      },
      resolveOutboundSessionRoute: (params) => {
        // If target starts with # → group board; otherwise direct DM
        const isBoard = params.to.startsWith("#");
        return buildChannelOutboundSessionRoute({
          peer: isBoard
            ? { kind: "group", id: params.to }
            : { kind: "direct", id: params.to },
          chatType: isBoard ? "group" : "direct",
          from: params.from,
          to: params.to,
          sessionKey: `${params.accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID}:${params.to}`,
          baseSessionKey: `${params.accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID}:${params.to}`,
        });
      },
    },
    status: {
      ...createComputedAccountStatusAdapter<ResolvedPulseboardAccount>({ ... }),
    },
    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        // 1. Validate account.configured
        // 2. Get runtime + create pairing controller
        // 3. Create PulseboardClient and call connect()
        // 4. In onDirectMessage handler:
        //      - Resolve DM access via resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime
        //      - Dispatch via dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime
        //      - deliver callback calls client.sendDirectMessage
        // 5. In onBoardMessage handler:
        //      - Apply group policy (groupPolicy: allowlist/open/disabled)
        //      - Dispatch via dispatchInboundReplyWithBase with ChatType: "group"
        //      - deliver callback calls client.sendBoardMessage
        // 6. Store client in activeClients map
        // 7. Return { stop: () => { client.disconnect(); activeClients.delete(accountId) } }
      },
    },
  },
  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseboardUsername",
      message: "Your pairing request has been approved!",
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => normalizePulseboardAllowEntry(entry) ?? entry,
      notify: async ({ id, message }) => {
        const client = activeClients.get(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID);
        if (client) await client.sendDirectMessage(id, message);
      },
    },
  },
  security: {
    resolveDmPolicy: resolvePulseboardDmPolicy,
  },
  outbound: {
    deliveryMode: "direct",
    textChunkLimit: 4000,
    sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId }) => {
      const aid = accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID;
      const client = activeClients.get(aid);
      if (!client) throw new Error(`PulseBoard client not running for account ${aid}`);
      // Resolve markdown table mode, convert tables
      const isBoard = to.startsWith("#");
      const result = isBoard
        ? await client.sendBoardMessage(to.slice(1), text ?? "")
        : await client.sendDirectMessage(to, text ?? "");
      return attachChannelToResult("pulseboard", {
        to,
        messageId: result.messageId,
      });
    },
  },
});
```

**Group dispatch detail** (inside `onBoardMessage` handler in `startAccount`):
- Check `account.config.groupPolicy` (default `"open"`): if `"disabled"`, drop; if `"allowlist"`, verify board is in `account.config.boards`
- Dispatch via `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` (import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch`) passing `ChatType: "group"`, `GroupSubject: boardName`

> **Import path note:** `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` lives in `src/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch.ts`. The package.json exports ~100+ SDK subpaths; verify the exact path name at implementation time. The IRC plugin accesses it via `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`; for PulseBoard, try `openclaw/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch` or `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-dispatch` as candidates.

